        "action": "Remove pay setting power for Council Leaders and Executives from local authority",
        "additional_details": "Walsall Council's Chief Executive is paid \u00a3198,562 \r\nDudley Council's Cheif Executive is paid \u00a3189,000 \r\nStaffordshire Council's Chief Executive is paid \u00a3203,393 \r\nWolverhampton Council's Chief Executive is paid \u00a3155,595 \r\nBedfordshire Borough Council's chief exec salary band is \u00a3156,075 - \u00a3173,417 and this is documented on their own website \r\n\r\nWhy should council tax payers money be spent like this when public services and infrastructure spending is being cut? Why should they be paid more than MPs?",
